article.headline: Siena 77, James Madison 66
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Michael Haddix scored 21 points and grabbed seven rebounds as Siena defeated James Madison 77-66 on Saturday night. Edwin Ubiles scored 11 of his 18 points in the first half as Siena led 36-24 at the break, with Dukes shooting 30 percent from the floor. In the second half, Matt Hilton's second 3-pointer cut Siena's lead to 55-51 with 9:43 to go, but the Saints scored on their next two possessions and made 11 of 12 free throws in the final six minutes. David Ryan had 14 points and Kenny Hasbrouck added 13 for Siena (17-10). Juwann James scored 19 points for James Madison (7-20) and grabbed eight rebounds. Terrance Carter had 14 points. Haddix made 9 of 10 free throws, shot 6-for-8 from the field and passed 1,500 career points.
